George's post reminded me of this link from the type2.com Library:
 
http://neptune.spacebears.com/cars/legal/oiladd.html#seven

Basically, Briggs and Stratton found that their engines would run just
fine without oil for 20 hours straight.  Upon tear-down there was some
bearing damage, though.  The article has more detail and the rest of it
is pretty good, too.

